<span class="pagehead">News :: News Highlights</span><br><br>
<span class="head">2003 CES News Highlights</span><br><br>

<b>Technology Policy a Major Focus at 2003 International CES</b><br>
Some 100 leaders of U.S. state and federal government are expected to travel to Las Vegas when the 2003 International 
CES returns to town, January 9-12. This group of U.S. policy makers is believed to be the largest group of its kind to 
attend any event outside Washington other than the political conventions.  Several activities, technology pavilions and 
conference sessions are planned to discuss technology policy directly related to the consumer electronics industry.<br> 
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=10032">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>2003 International CES Announces Special Incentives for International Attendees</b><br> 
The International CES, North America’s largest technology tradeshow, announced plans to cater to the show’s global audience before and during the 2003 show.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=10033">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Dell's Michael Dell to Deliver Industry Insider Presentation</b><br>
Michael Dell, chairman of the board and CEO of Dell Computer Corp., will deliver the first-ever International CES Industry 
Insider presentation on Thursday, January 9 at 3:00 p.m. in Room N250 of the Las Vegas Convention Center.<br> 
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=10025">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>International CES Expands Globally in 2003 </b><br> 
The 2003 International CES, North America’s largest technology tradeshow by a factor of two, returns to Las Vegas January 
9-12, 2003.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=10023">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>CES Issues Call for Innovations Entries</b><br> 
Entries for Innovations 2003, the consumer technology design awards program sponsored by the Consumer Electronics 
Association (CEA) and endorsed by the Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA), are being accepted until 
September 27, 2002.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=10016">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Sony's Kunitake Ando to Keynote Day 1 Morning</b><br> 
Kunitake ("Kuni") Ando, the president and COO of Sony Corp., will deliver the 2003 International CES Opening Keynote Address on Thursday, January 9 at 8:30 a.m. in the Las Vegas Hilton Theater.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9995">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Texas Instruments' Tom Engibous to Keynote at 2003 International CES</b><br> 
Tom Engibous, CEO of TI, will deliver a CES keynote address on Friday, January 10, 2003, at 4:30 p.m. in the Las Vegas Hilton Theater.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9994">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Intel's Craig Barrett to Keynote at 2003 International CES</b><br>
Craig Barrett, CEO of Intel Corporation, will deliver a CES keynote address on Thursday, January 9, 2003, at 4:30 p.m. in the Las Vegas Hilton Theater.<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9985">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>CES Issues Call for Conference Speakers</b><br>
CEA issued a call for speaker applications for the 2003 International CES.  Speaker proposals are due by August 2, 2002. <br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9975">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Microsoft’s Bill Gates Will Return to International CES </b><br>
Bill Gates, chairman and chief software architect for Microsoft Corp., will deliver the 2003 International CES Pre-Show Keynote Address on Wednesday, January 8, 2003 at 6:30 p.m. in Las Vegas.  <br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9977">Read all about it</a><br><br> 

<span class="head">2002 CES News Highlights</span><br><br>
<b>International CES Ranked Largest Show in the United States </b><br>
The 2001 International CES topped the Tradeshow Week 200, making it the largest tradeshow in the United States and Canada as ranked by <i>Tradeshow Week</i>.  <br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9951">Read all about it</a><br><br>

<b>Expomark Audit Reveals Growing B2B Community at CES </b><br>
While retailers remain the heart of the International CES audience, Expomark’s independent audit reveals a growing business-to-business (B2B) community at the show.  <br>
<a href="">Read all about it</a><br><br>
<a name="2002"></a>

<b>The Consensus Is In: 2002 International CES is a Phenomenal Success</b><br>
Attendees abuzz over latest and greatest in gaming, wireless, mobile, home networking, digital audio and video.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=9958" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>

<b>Education, Awareness and Professional Installation Cited as Keys to Home Networking Success at CES Supersession</b><br>
Realizing the goal of installing or retrofitting networks in every home requires coordination amongst multiple industries, panelists agreed during the Home Networking Supersession - The Builder Focus held here yesterday at the 2002 International CES.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8728" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>
 
<b>CEA and SAE Announce Partnership to Promote In-Car Connectivity</b><br>
In their opening remarks at the Car Technologies Supersession: The Road to Universal Automotive Electronics Connectivity, held yesterday at the 2002 International CES in Las Vegas, Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) President Neil Schilke and Gary Shapiro, president of the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) announced a partnership to leverage the synergy of the two groups to address on-board electronics, computerization and telematics.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8727" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>

<b>TechTV Announces Winners of Best of CES</b><br>
These awards recognize and honor the most outstanding new consumer technology products that debuted at the 2002 International CES.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8726" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>

<b>International CES Hosts Congressional Leaders in Spirited Debate on Technology Policy </b><br>
Attendees at the 2002 International CES - Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology - were treated to an event yesterday that is normally reserved for visitors to Capitol Hill, as Gary Shapiro, president and CEO of the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), moderated a spirited discussion among top Republican and Democratic elected officials on partisan politics and the development of technology policy.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8725" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>
 
<b>Esrey Outlines Future of Wireless in CES Keynote Address </b><br>
In today&#146;s morning keynote at the 2002 International CES - Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology - William T. Esrey, chairman and CEO of Sprint outlined the company&#146;s plans to be the first wireless carrier to deliver third generation (3G) wireless services nationwide.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8723" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="sprint%20keynote%20tarnscript.doc" class="bodylink">|transcript|</a>
<br><br>
 
<b>Chairman and CEO of Philips Gerard Kleisterlee Keynote </b><br>
Remarks from Chairman and CEO of Philips Gerard Kleisterlee given at the 2002 International CES Keynote Wednesday, January 9, 2002
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=7952" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="Gerard%20Kleisterlee%20keynote%20transcript.doc" class="bodylink">|transcript|</a>
<br><br>

<b>CES Retail Power Panelists Optimistic About 2002 CE Sales  </b><br>
The products and trends that accelerated sales of consumer electronics during the 2001 holiday season will help the industry reach record sales numbers in 2002, according to consumer electronics (CE) retail industry leaders participating in a panel discussion yesterday at the 2002 International Consumer Electronics Show (CES).
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8721" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>

<b>Fiorina Highlights Importance of Digital Imaging in Sharing the Human Experience at CES Keynote </b><br>
In yesterday afternoon&#146;s keynote at the 2002 International CES - Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology - Carly Fiorina, chairman and CEO of Hewlett-Packard (HP), described her company&#146;s role in the dynamic and rapidly growing digital imaging marketplace and underscored the importance of HP&#146;s proposed merger with Compaq.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8719" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="Fiorina%20keynote%20transcript.doc" class="bodylink">|transcript|</a>
<br><br>
 
<b>Digital Media Debate Holds Court at CES </b><br>
Attendees to the 2002 International CES-Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology - heard a spirited discussion of the proper balance between home recording and fair use rights, intellectual property, new technologies in the digital age and how these factions can be incorporated into new business models yesterday during the Digital Download: Cracking the Code to Profitability SuperSession.
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8718" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>
 
<b>Convergence of Wireless Devices to Multiply in 2002 </b><br>
Panelists at the Wireless SuperSession held yesterday at the 2002 International CES in Las Vegas, agreed a variety of intuitive wireless convergence products that are easier to use will emerge within the next 12 months. 
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8720" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
<br><br>

<b>Gary Shapiro's Keynote Address</b><br>
Remarks from Gary Shapiro President and CEO of the Consumer Electronics Association given at the 2002 International CES Opening Keynote Tuesday, January 8, 2002
<br>
<a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8716" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="CES%20Opening%20Press%20Copy_Gary.doc" class="bodylink">|transcript|</a>
<br><br>

<b>Gates Pre-Opens 2002 International CES with Vision of Digital Decade </b> <br>
Microsoft Corporation Chairman and Chief Software Architect Bill Gates pre-opened the 2002 International CES - Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology - with a dramatic presentation highlighting the role of software in defining the direction of electronics device design. 
<br><a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8714" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="Gates%20keynote%20transcript.doc" class="bodylink">|transcript|</a>
<br><br>

<b>Consumer Electronics Sales to Increase in 2002  </b> <br>
Sales of consumer electronics goods from manufacturers to dealers will surpass $95.7 billion in 2002, according to figures released today by the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA). 
<br><a href="/for_press_analysts/press_releases/display_rel.asp?id=8713" class="bodylink">Read all about it</a>
